===Etymology===
Uncertain; prob. from one of two jokes, one in which a protracted search for an alleged remarkably shaggy, talking dog ends in the discovery of the dog which, though it can indeed talk, is disappointingly not so shaggy after all; or one in which an even more protracted search for the shaggiest dog in the world ends in the utterly anticlimactic punchline "Now ''that's'' a shaggy dog!".

===Noun===
'''[[shaggy]] [[dog]] [[story]]'''
# A long-winded tale or [[yarn]] featuring extensive narration of typically irrelevant details, usually resulting in a pointless or absurd punchline, which is often a [[pun]] or [[Spoonerism]] on a known catchphrase.

